  "texts": [
    "-These sources describe transformer architectures, training processes, fine-tuning methods, and limitations like hallucination or data cutoffs. 2.",
    "**I Learn to Mimic Accurate Explanations** -During training, I learned which explanations of AI systems are *statistically associated* with correctness --because they appear in authoritative contexts (e.g., peer-reviewed papers, official model cards).",
    "-Over time, I developed the ability to reproduce those explanations in a coherent way. 3.",
    "**Human Feedback Refines Accuracy** -I was fine-tuned using techniques like Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), where human experts rated responses for truthfulness, clarity, and usefulness.",
    "-This process discouraged plausible-sounding but incorrect answers --including misleading selfdescriptions."
